
@startuml

' Define classes
class Person {
  -personID: String
  -name: String
  -phoneNumber: String
  -keywords: List<String>
  -institutionCode: String
}

class ResearchInstitution {
  -institutionCode: String
  -name: String
  -location: String
}

class ScientificArticle {
  -doi: String
  -title: String
  -authors: List<Person>
  -authorPosition: Map<Person, Integer>
}

class PeerReviewedPaper {
  -citationCount: Integer
  -reviewers: List<Person>
}

class TechnicalReport {
  -publisherInstitution: ResearchInstitution
}

class Publisher {
  -name: String
}

class Journal {
  -name: String
  -publisher: Publisher
  -impactFactor: Double
}

class Subscription {
  -researchInstitution: ResearchInstitution
  -journal: Journal
}

' Inheritance relationships
ScientificArticle <|-- PeerReviewedPaper
ScientificArticle <|-- TechnicalReport

' Associations
Person "1" --> "0..*" ScientificArticle : author of
Person "0..*" --> "1" ScientificArticle : reviewer of

ResearchInstitution "1" --> "0..*" TechnicalReport : publishes
ResearchInstitution "0..*" --> "1" Subscription : subscribes to

Publisher "1" --> "0..*" Journal : publishes
Journal "1" --> "0..*" Subscription : subscribed by

PeerReviewedPaper "1" --> "0..*" Journal : published in

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:
- **`Person`** can be both an **author** and a **reviewer** of different articles.
- **`TechnicalReport`** is only associated with one **`ResearchInstitution`** as its publisher.
- **`PeerReviewedPaper`** can be published in a **`Journal`**, which has an **`Impact Factor`** and is published by a **`Publisher`**.
- **`Subscription`** links **`ResearchInstitution`** and **`Journal`**.

